        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 4:37PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 437 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from 10 miles northwest of San Acacia to
near Socorro, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Socorro, Lemitar, San Acacia, Escondida, La Joya, Bernardo,
Chamizal, Contreras, Luis Lopez and Abeytas.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 60 between Mile Markers 121 and 169.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 143 and 179.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Blowing dust associated with strong thunderstorm winds can reduce
visibility below one quarter mile at times.</instruction>
